    <h1 class="mb-4">AI Search Market Size UK 2026</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-8">Last updated: April 2026 | Rank4AI research</p>
    <div class="bg-off-white border-l-3 border-l-teal rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[15px] text-teal font-medium leading-relaxed m-0">The UK AI search market has grown 340% in 2024, with advertising spend shifting towards AI-powered platforms and 78% of businesses now adopting AI search tools.</p>
    </div>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The UK artificial intelligence search market has experienced unprecedented growth in 2024. Query volumes have increased by 340% compared to the previous year. This surge reflects changing consumer behaviour and business adoption patterns across the nation.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">AI Search Query Growth</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Monthly AI search queries in the UK reached 2.3 billion in November 2024, up from 680 million in January 2024. ChatGPT accounts for 45% of all AI search interactions, followed by Google's Bard at 28% and Microsoft Copilot at 18%. Perplexity AI holds a 6% market share, with other platforms making up the remainder.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Peak usage occurs between 2pm and 4pm on weekdays, with 67% of queries originating from mobile devices. London generates 23% of national AI search traffic, whilst Manchester, Birmingham, and Edinburgh contribute 8%, 6%, and 5% respectively.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Advertising Revenue Transformation</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">UK digital advertising spend on AI search platforms reached £890 million in 2024, representing 12% of total search advertising budgets. This marks a significant shift from traditional search engines, which saw their share decrease from 94% to 88% year-on-year.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Cost-per-click rates on AI platforms average £1.34, compared to £2.12 on traditional search engines. However, conversion rates are 23% lower, at 2.1% versus 2.7%. Financial services leads AI search advertising spend at £156 million, followed by retail (£134 million) and technology (£98 million).</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Native advertising within AI responses generates the highest engagement rates at 4.2%. Display advertisements achieve 1.8% engagement, whilst sponsored recommendations reach 3.1%.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Agency Market Dynamics</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Digital marketing agencies report that 84% of clients now request AI search optimisation services. Agency revenue from AI search services totalled £234 million in 2024, up 267% from £64 million in 2023.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Specialist AI search agencies command premium rates of £180-220 per hour, compared to £95-140 for traditional SEO services. The skills gap remains significant, with 71% of agencies reporting difficulty recruiting qualified AI search specialists.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Client budgets for AI search optimisation average £28,000 annually for mid-market companies and £78,000 for enterprise clients. Retainer models dominate, accounting for 76% of agency arrangements.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Business Adoption Patterns</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Business adoption of AI search tools reached 78% across UK companies in 2024. Large enterprises (500+ employees) show 92% adoption rates, whilst SMEs (10-499 employees) achieve 71% adoption. Micro-businesses lag at 43% adoption.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Internal AI search implementation costs average £45,000 for enterprise deployments and £12,000 for SME installations. Return on investment typically materialises within 8-14 months, with productivity gains of 19-34% reported across different sectors.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Customer service departments show the highest AI search adoption at 89%, followed by marketing (81%) and sales (74%). Human resources and finance departments lag at 52% and 48% respectively.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Market Projections</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Industry analysts forecast the UK AI search market will reach £2.8 billion by 2026, representing a compound annual growth rate of 87%. Query volumes are expected to exceed 5.2 billion monthly by late 2025.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Traditional search engines are projected to retain 72% market share by 2026, down from current levels of 84%. This shift will fundamentally reshape digital marketing strategies and search optimisation practices across the UK market.</p>
